Function Reference/comment author url link « WordPress Codex
-----------

Displays the comment author's [URL](/Glossary#URI_and_URL "Glossary")
(usually their web site), linked, if one was provided. This tag must be
within [The Loop](/The_Loop "The Loop"), or a comment loop.

Use
[get\_comment\_author\_url\_link](/index.php?title=Template_Tags/get_comment_author_url_link&action=edit&redlink=1 "Template Tags/get comment author url link (page does not exist)")
to retrieve the value.

Usage
-----

`  <?php comment_author_url_link('linktext', 'before', 'after'); ?> `

Examples
--------

### Default Usage

    web site: <?php comment_author_url_link(); ?><br />

### Link Text and Styling

Displays comment author's URL as text string **Visit Site of Comment
Author** and adds bullets before and after the link to style it.

    <?php comment_author_url_link('Visit Site of Comment Author', ' &bull; ', ' &bull; '); ?>

• [Visit Site of Comment Author](#Link_Text_and_Styling) •

Parameters
----------

 linktext 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    Link text for the link. Default is the comment author's URL.
 before 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    Text to display before the link. There is no default.
 after 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    Text to display after the link. There is no default.

